5. My conclusion

Based on everything you've shared:

✅ SR-IOV resources are configured correctly.

✅ HugePages are sufficient.

✅ Memory is sufficient.

✅ PerformanceProfile is correct.

❌ The only blocker is that the node has 108 allocatable CPUs, while the workload plus system pods leave less than 5 CPUs available for pmp0.


If this Samsung BSCF deployment is expected to run all eight CNFs (including pmp0) on a 112-core SNO, then either:

the vendor's sizing assumes lower CPU requests for one or more components, or

the host is expected to have more allocatable CPUs.


If this is Samsung's reference deployment, I'd recommend comparing your BSCF Helm values (or deployment manifests) with the reference values, especially the CPU requests for pmp0, bpp0, and bpp1. A small difference of 1–2 CPUs in one component is enough to prevent pmp0 from scheduling.
